<hr id="hr38"><p id="p39"><em>MacStories launched its first podcast in 2017 with <a href="https://www.macstories.net/podcasts/appstories/" rel="noopener noreferrer">AppStories</a>. Since then, the lineup has expanded to include a family of weekly shows that also includes <a href="https://www.macstories.net/unwind/" rel="noopener noreferrer">MacStories Unwind</a>, <a href="https://www.macstories.net/magic-rays-of-light/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Magic Rays of Light</a>, <a href="https://www.macstories.net/comfort-zone/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Comfort Zone</a>, <a href="https://www.macstories.net/npc/" rel="noopener noreferrer">NPC: Next Portable Console</a>, and <a href="https://www.macstories.net/first-last-everything/" rel="noopener noreferrer">First, Last, Everything</a> that collectively, cover a broad range of the modern media world from Apple’s streaming service and videogame hardware to apps for a growing audience that appreciates our thoughtful, in-depth approach to media.</em></p>
<p id="p40"><em>If you’re interested in advertising on our shows, you can learn more <a href="https://www.macstories.net/advertise/" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a> or by contacting our Managing Editor, <a href="mailto:voorhees@macstories.net" rel="noopener noreferrer">John Voorhees</a>.</em></p>
